Operations Management Training Consultant
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/06 07:16:39
Ref. JB3047734
Job Description
With clients all over the Middle & Far East, Europe and Africa this Training and Management Consultancy has a fantastic reputation in the market. An extremely high retention rate, fantastic multinational clients, great work life balance and truly professional Consultants make this an employer of choice.
The role is to provide exceptional Operations Training to major multinational businesses across the region, and you will design and deliver bespoke training programs, based around a multitude of backgrounds, including Supply Chain, Manufacturing, Maintenance and Project Management.
The candidates that are being sought for this role must be of the highest caliber and will in return receive an excellent benefits package with a longer term equity offering, and one of the best work life balances in the Middle East.
Skills
We require:
- An Arabic speaker, able to travel to Saudi easily
- 7+ years in a major multinational organization in 2 of the following disciplines: Supply Chain, Production, Maintenance, Projects, Contracts or Quality Management.
- A highly polished and well presented individual with excellent Arabic and English skills
- A Master's degree or a PhD from a recognized university (One of the Degrees should be in Engineering)
- Exceptional presentation and coaching skills
- Experience of providing training to Supply Chain Professionals
